item.title: Black Mesa : The Comic, What Makes a Man
item.dc:creator: ijgs
item.description:
Outstanding work Jon! Made me chuckle and was intelligently done. Bravo good sirrah, bravo!

Although I must say, if you hadn’t told us you were aiming for Dostoyevski, I personally would have pegged it as a pitch perfect pastiche (ooh, aliteration much?!) of the interplay between Hamlet, Rosencrantz & Guildenstern… nevertheless, bloody marvelous all round old chap![/SIZE]

Soup:

My personal favourite is meese, for the plural of moose.

I’m seriously trying to promote “shoop” as the correct singular of “sheep”… I mean, it’s not like the English language couldn’t do with a bit more consistency…
